OL,3,CWarning of rising cases of
OL,4,Ctuberculosis in Harrow
OL,6,FHarrow is the borough with the second
OL,7,Fhighest number of cases of
OL,8,FTuberculosis (TB) in England.
OL,10,FFourty-four in every 100,000 residents
OL,11,Fhave active Tuberculosis (TB)
OL,12,Faccording to the National TB
OL,13,FSurveillance System.
OL,15,FCases of TB in other areas of
OL,16,FNorthwest London is also high.
OL,17,FHowever, this seems to be levelling
OL,18,Foff whereas Harrow council says that
OL,19,Fits cases "still seem to be rising".
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G1/6
