CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F403A1773668260
OL,3,CWarning of rising cases of
OL,4,Ctuberculosis in Harrow
OL,6,FIt suggests that the disease
OL,7,Fdisproportionately affects people from
OL,8,FAsian communities and from more
OL,9,Fdeprived backgrounds.
OL,11,FPeople are more likely to get
OL,12,Ftuberculosis if they live in an area
OL,13,Fwhere it is more common, have a
OL,14,Fweakened immune system or spend a lot
OL,15,Fof time with someone who has active TB.
OL,17,FChildren under five are also at higher
OL,18,Frisk of getting tuberculosis.
OL,20,FWhat is tuberculosis?
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G3/6
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
